          <div id="en-intro">
            <p><a href="/"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/me.webp" decoding="async" />Simon Park</a> is a software engineer who lives with agility.
              He often <a href="https://parksb.github.io/article/32.html">shaves yak</a> as a hobby.</p>
            <p>He previously interned as a front-end developer at <a href="https://www.navercorp.com/"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/naver.webp" decoding="async" />Naver</a> AjaxUI Lab and
              worked as a back-end engineer at <a href="https://kakaostyle.com/"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/kakao.webp" decoding="async" />Kakaostyle</a> Zigzag UX Group.
              Now he is majoring in digital media at <a href="https://www.ajou.ac.kr/"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/ajou.webp" decoding="async" />Ajou University</a>.</p>
            <p>He is interested in all fields of computer science, but he is particularly interested in HCI, HCC, and UX. He loves open-source culture, and he is donating to
              <img class="icon" src="/images/icons/mozilla.webp" decoding="async" /><a href="https://foundation.mozilla.org/">Mozilla Foundation</a>.
              He agrees with the design and philosophy of <img class="icon" src="/images/icons/rust.webp" decoding="async" /><a href="https://www.rust-lang.org/">Rust</a>, and writes code based on a functional programming paradigm.
              He works almost everything on <img class="icon" src="/images/icons/neovim.webp" decoding="async" /><a href="https://neovim.io/">NeoVim</a>. Additionally, he can deal with vector graphics.</p>
            <p>Feel free to contact him via <a href="mailto:parkgds@gmail.com">parkgds@gmail.com</a>.
              To explore his open-source contributions, you can visit his <a href="https://github.com/parksb"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/github.webp" decoding="async" />GitHub</a> profile.
              Also, you can find him on <a href="https://twitter.com/caesiumpark"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/twitter.webp" decoding="async" />Twitter</a> and
              <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/parksb"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/linkedin.webp" decoding="async" />LinkedIn</a>.
              If you need his PGP public key, you can find it on <a href="https://keybase.io/parksb"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/keybase.webp" decoding="async" />Keybase</a>.
              You can receive new articles from this website by subscribing to <a href="https://parksb.github.io/feed.xml"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/rss.webp" decoding="async" />RSS</a>.</p>
            <p>He reads books when he is free. You can check out his list of books to read, currently reading, and already read on
              his <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1gq1lIyUSIiKE_4YHhc_vkIVH_LzZA4Zk9aIHFzib2yA"><img class="icon" src="/images/icons/spreadsheet.webp" decoding="async" />bookshelf</a>.</p>
